http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/Gang-of-cheats-busted/article14019938.ece

A government schoolteacher laid a trap to apprehend two men of a gang involved in cheating dozens like him on the pretext of offering leave travel concession (LTC) packages. The suspects were handed over to the police with two more men being arrested later.“The kingpin of the gang was revealed to be one Pankaj Kumar. He had formed a travel agency with the intention to cheat unsuspecting teachers,” said Mandeep S Randhawa, DCP (South-East).Police said the gang targeted teachers in the areas like Jaitpur and Badarpur in South-East Delhi. So far, 17 such complaints have been received against this gang. —Staff Reporter